        <!-- required; can be short -->
        <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>

            <p>Böll was born in Cologne, Germany on December 21, 1917. During the 1930s, his family
                opposed the rise of Nazism and he refused to join the Hitler Youth. He was
                apprenticed to a bookseller before studying German at the University of Cologne.
                Conscripted into the Wehrmacht, he served in France, Romania, Hungary and the Soviet
                Union, and was wounded four times before being captured by United States armed
                forces in April 1945 and sent to a POW camp. Böll became a full-time writer at the
                age of 30. His first novel, <title render="italic">Der Zug war pünktlich</title>
                <title render="italic">(The Train Was on Time),</title> was
                published in 1949, and in 1972 he received the Nobel Prize for Literature.</p>

        </bioghist>

